> Pita pockets are sandwich superheroes. They're light, fluffy, and hold pretty
> much anything you want in their roomy pockets—so if you're going to make a
> pita sandwich, it better be fully loaded. This one does not disappoint: The
> whole wheat pitas are stuffed with a creamy feta spread, lemony chicken, and
> a crunchy Greek salad. Oh, and one more beautiful thing? We're sending
> fully-cooked chicken breasts so you'll spend less time in the kitchen—this
> recipe takes just 15 minutes from start to finish. Talk about pita perfection!

Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Roma Tomato{1} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Trim and
halve @Persian Cucumber{1} lengthwise; thinly slice crosswise into halfmoons.
Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Shallot{1}. Zest and halve @Lemon{1}. Peel and
grate or mince @Garlic{1%clove}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine tomato, cucumber, half the shallot, juice from
half the lemon, and a drizzle of @Olive Oil{4%tsp}. Season with @Salt{} and
@Pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{4%tbsp}, @Feta Cheese{1/2%cup},
a large drizzle of olive oil, and a pinch of garlic. Season with salt and
pepper.

Thinly slice @Standard Meat™ Cast-Iron Seared Chicken Breasts{9%oz} crosswise.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add remaining
shallot; cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in chicken, lemon zest, remaining garlic, juice from remaining lemon, and
pepper. Cook, stirring, until chicken is warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Turn
off heat.

Microwave @Whole Wheat Pitas{2} until warm and pliable, ~{10-15%seconds}; halve
crosswise to create pockets. Spread insides of pita pockets with feta spread,
then fill with as much chicken and salad as will fit.

Divide pita pockets between plates. Serve any remaining chicken and salad on
the side.